The paper deals with stochastic network design, which involves optimization and decision-making under uncertainty. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.RO (robotics), and cs.SI (social and information networks). The focus on river network optimization and spatial conservation planning suggests that cs.DS and cs.RO are likely categories, while the use of imprecise data and robust optimization techniques suggests cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the interdisciplinary nature of the paper and its potential applications in sustainability and environmental science suggest cs.SI as a possible category.
